FBIS4-46295 "jptot023__l94081" JPRS-TOT-94-023-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 30 May 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Carbomb Kills Chechen Minister, Wounds President Carbomb Kills Chechen Minister, Wounds President `Remote Control Device' Used LD3005111494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1000 GMT 30 May 94 LD3005111494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [Text] Chechnya President Dzhokhar Dudayev's wife and young son received injuries of varying degrees of severity during the assassination attempt on the president on 28 May, according to a statement released by the Chechnya Foreign Ministry today. The Foreign Ministry assesses the act of terrorism, in which the republic's interior minister and his deputy were killed, as an attack on President Dudayev. The terrorists used a remote control explosive device, which the Russian special services have at their disposal.
